                                <summary>20 quires of 8 folia, except for Quire 2 - 1f. (f. 1);
                                    Quire 17 - 7 ff. (ff. 114-119; 121) ; Quire 18 - 6 ff. (ff.
                                    122-127); Quire 19 - 6 ff. (ff. 128-133); Quire 20 - 4 ff. (ff.
                                    134-137); Quire 21 - 4 ff. (ff. 138-141)</summary>
                                <quire xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0" n="1">
                                    <extent xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">1</extent>
                                </quire>
                                <quire xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0" n="2-16">
                                    <extent xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">8</extent>
                                </quire>
                                <quire xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0" n="17">
                                    <extent xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">7</extent>
                                </quire>
                                <quire xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0" n="18-19">
                                    <extent xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">6</extent>
                                </quire>
                                <quire xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0" n="20-21">
                                    <extent xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">4</extent>
                                </quire>
                                <signatures>Original, in the outer corner of the bottom margin. It's
                                    marked with black or red ink</signatures>
                            </collation>
                            <condition>The end and probably the beginning of the MS are missing; the
                                book also lacks some folia between ff. 1 and 2, one folio between
                                ff. 113 and 114, as well as some folia from the last damaged 4
                                quires. F. 120 was taken from another MS probably when the MS was
                                copied</condition>
                        </supportDesc>
                        <layoutDesc>
                            <layout columns="1" writtenLines="20">19 lines on f. 120</layout>
                        </layoutDesc>
                    </objectDesc>
                    <ink xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0">Black, in some places
                        with yellowish brown shadow</ink>
                    <decoDesc>
                        <decoNote type="headpieces">There are headpieces in braided Balkan style on
                            ff. 18v, 21r, 35v, 56v, some of them with an arch-form - on ff. 1r,
                            23r</decoNote>
                        <decoNote type="initials">Many large initials: in braided Balkan style on
                            ff. 1v, 4v, 5v, 6v, 8r, 9r, 11r, etc.; and in new-Byzantine style with
                            floral motifs on ff. 3r, 31v, 36r, 37r, 39r, etc. A red initial in
                            new-Byzantine style with floral motifs on f. 120</decoNote>
                    </decoDesc>
                    <bindingDesc>
                        <binding>
                            <p>Old, probably original binding - wooden panels covered with
                                ornamented leather</p>
                        </binding>
                    </bindingDesc>
